  "text": "In our second analysis, we aimed to find out whether low preoperative 25-OHD level affected the accuracy of single qPTH in predicting hypocalcemia by comparing the AUC of PTH-SC when 25-OHD\\15 ng/mL with the AUC of PTH-SC when 25-OHD C15 ng/mL. However, unlike a previous study reporting that the AUC of qPTH was lower in 25-OHD \\10 ng/mL than in C10 ng/mL (0.68 vs. 0.93), we found that the two groups had similar accuracy by AUC (0.88 vs. 0.85, p = 0.61). [CITATION_1] This was despite our study having a significant larger cohort. In other words, PTH-SC had similar accuracy in predicting postthyroidectomy hypocalcemia regardless of whether the preoperative 25-OHD was\\15 or C15 ng/mL. However, because the number of studies focusing on this issue is small, our finding requires further confirmation by future prospective studies.",
